<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC "-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN" "http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd">
<html xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
    <head>
        <title>CSS Test: Setting a percentage 'height' on cell computes to 'auto'</title>
        <link rel="author" title="Microsoft" href="http://www.microsoft.com/" />
        <link rel="help" href="http://www.w3.org/TR/CSS21/tables.html#height-layout" />
        <meta name="flags" content="ahem" />
        <meta name="assert" content="A percentage 'height' value on a table cell computes to 'auto'." />
        <style type="text/css">
            table
            {
                background: black;
                border-spacing: 0;
                height: 4em;
            }
            td
            {
                background: black;
                font: 20px/1em ahem;
                padding: 0;
            }
            #cell
            {
                background: blue;
                color: blue;
                height: 50%;
            }
        </style>
    </head>
    <body>
        <p>Test passes if the blue and black boxes below are not the same height.</p>
        <table>
            <tr>
                <td id="cell">XXXXXXXXXX</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
                <td>XXXXXXXXXX</td>
            </tr>
        </table>
    </body>
</html>